0immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%20about%20why%20they%20didn't%20sign%20onto%20the%20brief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brief%20was%20filed%20in%20support%20of%20Perkins%20Coie%2C%20a%20law%20firm%20whose%20attorneys%20Trump%20effectively%20deemed%20a%20national%20security%20threat%20in%20an%20executive%20order%20that%20barred%20them%20from%20federal%20buildings%2C%20stripped%20them%20of%20security%20clearances%2C%20and%20required%20government%20contractors%20to%20disclose%20whether%20they%20used%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20former%20partners%20at%20Perkins%20Coie%20represented%20some%20of%20Trump's%20political%20adversaries%2C%20but%20most%20of%20the%20firm's%20political%20lawyers%20have%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20big%20firms%20did%20sign%20on%20to%20the%20brief%2C%20as%20did%20some%20top%20class-action%20lawyers%20and%20trial%20lawyers%20who%20often%20represent%20plaintiffs%20suing%20big%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20arm%20of%20Freshfields%2C%20a%20UK-founded%20corporate%20law%20firm%20that%20last%20year%20was%20reported%20to%20do%20about%2020%25%20of%20its%20business%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20signed%20the%20brief.%20Arnold%20%26amp%3B%20Porter%2C%20a%20big%20DC-based%20firm%20that%20represented%20federal%20workers%20accused%20of%20being%20communists%20during%20the%20%26quot%3BRed%20Scare%26quot%3B%20of%20the%201950s%2C%20also%20included%20its%20name.%20Arnold%20%26amp%3B%20Porter%20was%20one%20of%20eight%20firms%20among%20the%20country's%20100%20highest-earning%20that%20signed%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FLaw.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELaw.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20firms%20targeted%20by%20Trump's%20orders%20rallied%20behind%20Perkins.%20Covington%20%26amp%3B%20Burling%2C%20which%20gave%20legal%20advice%20to%20a%20prosecutor%20who%20went%20after%20Trump%2C%20as%20well%20as%20WilmerHale%20and%20Jenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%2C%20which%20have%20sued%20the%20Trump%20administration%20over%20executive%20orders%20that%20targeted%20them%2C%20all%20put%20their%20names%20on%20the%20brief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20lack%20of%20America's%20largest%20firms%20was%20frustrating%2C%20said%20Eimer%2C%20who%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20didn't%20know%20whose%20names%20would%20be%20included%20until%20shortly%20before%20the%20legal%20papers%20were%20filed%20because%20the%20process%20was%20treated%20with%20extreme%20confidentiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20understand%2C%20from%20the%20management%20side%2C%20why%20they%20feel%20that%20jeopardizing%20their%20business%20is%20their%20overriding%20concern.%20But%20in%20my%20view%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20lawyers%20have%20an%20obligation%20to%20the%20courts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20the%20constitution%20that%20overrides%20our%20business%20interest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaw%20firms%2C%20including%20Skadden%20Arps%20Slate%20Meagher%20%26amp%3B%20Flom%2C%20Milbank%2C%20and%20Willkie%20Farr%20%26amp%3B%20Gallagher%2C%20have%20cut%20deals%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20collectively%20devote%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20worth%20of%20lawyers'%20time%20to%20causes%20that%20dovetail%20with%20the%20president's%20interests%20%E2%80%94%20like%20veterans'%20rights%20and%20fighting%20antisemitism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloomberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bloomberglaw.com%2Fus-law-week%2Fconservative-group-solicits-free-aid-from-big-law-amid-attacks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20conservative%20group%20The%20Oversight%20Project%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20law%20firms%20asking%20them%20to%20donate%20up%20to%20%2410%20million%20of%20legal%20advice%20to%20it%20and%20other%20%26quot%3Bcenter-right%26quot%3B%20groups%20to%20help%20satisfy%20their%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20firm%20to%20cut%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%20was%20%3